    <sec id="SEC2-3">
      <title>Bisulphite sequencing</title>
      <p>Fastq files obtained by MiSeq system (Illumina) were trimmed with <italic>cutadapt</italic> software (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://cutadapt.readthedocs.io/en/stable/">http://cutadapt.readthedocs.io/en/stable/</ext-link>) using quality (<monospace>-q 30</monospace>) and short reads (<monospace>-m 50</monospace>) parameters. Trimmed reads were aligned with <italic>bismark</italic> software using human reference build hg19 (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/bismark/">https://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/bismark/</ext-link>). Finally, to extract the methylation level per every single cytosine, we used the tool <italic>bismark_methylation_extractor</italic> included in the <italic>bismark</italic> package.</p>
